newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline slightly weaker in dull market.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline slightly weaker in dull market.

text.p: NWE gasoline was flat to slightly weaker on Thursday in a lacklustre market, traders said.
"It's very dull," said one trader. Eurograde barges traded at $197 fob Rotterdam for prompt to May 15 delivery early on and at $194.50 and $195 fob ARA for promptish material later on.
May swaps were heard done at $194.50 and $194.75 in late trade. A parcel of prompt regular material traded at $189.50.
Some sellers continued to stay out of the market in the expectation of strengthening prices over the next few days.
On the cargo front, Scandinavian players were looking into supplying demand out of Poland, traders said.

Very little material appeared to be heading for the United States, partly because the arbitrage door was barely ajar and partly because few players had enough material for the 60,000 tonne cargo needed to make the trip worthwhile, trader said.
